title: How to help Cyclone Mocha victims
description: One of the strongest storms ever to hit Myanmar has left thousands of people in urgent need of food, water, shelter, and medical assistance.

title: The world's largest lakes are shrinking dramatically, and scientists say they have figured out why
description: More than half of the world's largest lakes and reservoirs have lost significant amounts of water over the last three decades.

title: What really happened during Prince Harry and Meghan's New York car chase?
description: There's no denying the echoes to the late Princess Diana's 1997 death in a car crash in Paris. More than 25 years on, her son and his wife were pursued through the streets of New York City this week in what their team called a "near catastrophic" car chase.

title: UN expert says Myanmar imported $1 billion in arms since coup
description: Myanmar's ruling military junta has imported at least $1 billion in weapons and military-related equipment since its bloody coup, according to a new United Nations report which said much of the equipment was coming from individuals and businesses in Russia, China and Singapore.
